<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5464: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received October 24, 11:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[From <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at Omsk:]</p>
                        <p>437, October 23, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>Colonel <persName>Johnson</persName> here in Omsk has just received the
                            following instruction from <persName corresp="#p_ECGH1">Colonel
                                Emerson</persName> in Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“As fast as Czechs evacuate back of railway which they are now
                                    patrolling you will withdraw all technical inspectors with
                                    them.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>The importance of this instruction and the unfortunate impressions it
                            will undoubtedly make on the Russian people is something which the
                            Department may imagine and upon which it is unnecessary for me to
                            comment. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>